race.comment: A small field but a good race. MISHANI EGO (5) won a trial and then took out a 65 at the Sunshine Coast first-up enjoying the return to a good track. Ran a decent number and Ben Thompson is a key jockey engagement replacing the apprentice. She's proven second-up and can go on with the job. CABALETTO (6) raced a $3.2F and was much too good for the CL1 graders at Toowoomba first-up leading from pillar to post. She's now won 2/3 and Huxtable stays aboard and will use the inside gate. She has plenty of scope for improvement. DREAM SMART (3) resumes off a comfortable win in a 70 at Rockhampton over 1400m. She's trialled well and is right up to this at best. The betting will be key. MERCIAN (2) was backed off the map winning a CL1 at the Sunshine Coast. Loses Thompson but hits the race at peak and also has claims.
